quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  7,164,"When some of ňĻthe righteous amongňļ them questioned ňĻtheir fellow Sabbath-keepersňļ, ‚ÄúWhy do you ňĻbother toňļ warn those ňĻSabbath-breakersňļ who will either be destroyed or severely punished by Allah?‚ÄĚ They replied, ‚ÄúJust to be free from your Lord‚Äôs blame, and so perhaps they may abstain.‚ÄĚ"
  7,165,"When they ignored the warning they were given, We rescued those who used to warn against evil and overtook the wrongdoers with a dreadful punishment for their rebelliousness"
  7,166,"But when they stubbornly persisted in violation, We said to them, ‚ÄúBe disgraced apes!‚ÄĚ"
  7,167,"And ňĻremember, O Prophet,ňļ when your Lord declared that He would send against them others who would make them suffer terribly until the Day of Judgment. Indeed, your Lord is swift in punishment, but He is certainly All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  7,168,"We dispersed them through the land in groups‚ÄĒsome were righteous, others were less so. We tested them with prosperity and adversity, so perhaps they would return ňĻto the Right Pathňļ"
  7,169,"Then they were succeeded by other generations who inherited the Scripture. They indulged in unlawful gains, claiming, ‚ÄúWe will be forgiven ňĻafter allňļ.‚ÄĚ And if similar gain came their way, they would seize it. Was a covenant not taken from them in the Scripture that they would not say anything about Allah except the truth? And they were already well-versed in its teachings. But the ňĻeternalňļ Home of the Hereafter is far better for those mindful ňĻof Allahňļ. Will you not then understand"
  7,170,As for those who firmly abide by the Scripture and establish prayer‚ÄĒsurely We never discount the reward of those acting righteously